premise_source_doc_sentence: John Winston Ono Lennon ,  (  born John Winston Lennon ; 9 October 19408 December 1980  )  was an English guitarist , singer , and songwriter who co-founded the Beatles , the most commercially successful and musically influential band in the history of popular music .
